vid Schmucker',0,'2012-01-02 19:17:25','2012-01-02 19:17:25'),(93,81,'Thank you for helping us after the September fires. Now we are rebuilding and could use your help and prayers again. I know you must get many requests, so I understand the scope of these times of hardship. Thank-you again,and keep us in your thoughts and prayers.  Linda',0,'2012-01-02 21:18:46','2012-01-02 21:18:46'),(94,82,'     Dear beloved friends in Christ,                                  \r\n      First and foremost, I  bring  my warmest greeting to you in our blessed hope of Jesus Christ. God\'s grace and peace be with you. \r\n      Every new day declares the breath and beauty of God\'s creation. It seems that when people stop doing charity the whole human relationship will get dry. So that in this day and age, it sometimes seems that graced people doing faith  things are becoming a few and very far at these end times. That is why it is so refreshing knowing some body like you ! \r\n    Though We don\'t have any acquaintance because there is the biggest geographical gap between us , but  it is known the most important historical event for us was not the walking on the moon, but that JESUS OF NAZARETH walked on the earth. As the bible says in Rev. 5: 9-10 we are linked in the great family of God by this redemptive and holy history of our Lord Jesus Christ. Therefore I am so encouraged to email for you . \r\n      I love Jesus Christ and his savants more than this world glory and treasures. All glory and honor back to the sweet name of the one who chose the path of obedience, not expedience. It is  really a big privilege and opportunity to be the servant for the living God. I am so pleased with the Lord since he has used you in a mighty way bring out the truth of God. \r\n     Dear the people  of God, I have a profound thirst to know more about God and his word through your gracious  ministries , but I am deeply sorry that even I couldn’t really  buy any study bibles. So that I am not fortunate and being severely suffered to get any  Christ-Centered books.   As a Christian minister, it is not expected from me to break your hearts, but truth can’t break us because it is stranger than fiction: there is a time that a simple coin needed to buy a piece of paper. That is why I decided to send this message for you by considering that my prayer answer is in your hands. \r\n        Here in Addis Ababa , there are so many various denominational churches. Over 95% gospel ministers have no reasonable personal libraries to study the truth of the Holy Scriptures. 80% know nothing about the holy bible and its major teachings. The work of evangelism is not being done in a biblical way. In many charismatic meetings the crucified and risen  Jesus is hardly mentioned and exalted. The name of man is being glorified.  By these situations most of us is being tossed about by every wind of doctrine and irrational teachings . \r\n       Dear beloved people God, there are so many people who reject the gospel of Christ and how many have turned away from the scriptural teaching.  Sadly this is a great problem I face with many people , to whom I know individually and others  even so called ministers of gospel have turned away from the word of God and only teach the word of men. Oh, brethrens,  may the  sovereign Lord protect us form ever departing from the all source of truth of his word !  Ethiopia  should  be helpful country ! \r\n      One of my passion is to share God\'s love and teach his truth to people here and sometimes I serve the Lord as gospel singer. Today many people are ashamed of Christ. The wise are ashamed of it, because it calls men to believe and not to argue; the great are ashamed of it, because it brings all into one body; the rich are ashamed of it, because it is to be had without money and without price; and so the good news of the glorious Son of God having come into the world a surety for lost sinners, is despised, uncared for, men are ashamed of it. Who are not ashamed of it ? \r\n     A little company, those whose hearts the Spirit of God has touched. They were once like the world and of it; but he awakened them to see their sin and misery, and that Christ alone was refuge, and now they cry, None but CHRIST ! And then, I am not ashamed of the gospel of Christ as the Paul of JESUS said in Rom. 1:16. \r\n   Dear beloved Sirs, you see, we can’t learn something with nothing. A student can not learn without a teacher. Likewise, a Christian minister can’t teach if he doesn’t study, and he can’t read or study if he doesn’t have books. Thus, books are the key to raising the standard of teaching in the body of Christ.    \r\n      Hope that your unreserved help will play a paramount role for my personal studies and ministries. So please send me whatever biblical and theological Christ-centered books, even if used. And at any time getting any basic need is not my burning issue. The others will come step by step as written in Mathew 4:4  if I get the WORD. \r\n     May our good and gracious God continue to give you health and enough strength for your everyday work as you live to please HIM. \r\n                                                                               \r\n              \r\n                  Yours truly in his glorious service,   \r\n             Evangelist & teacher  Abebe   Tsegaye \r\n      \r\n       \r\n  \r\n  \r\n        My address:-       Abebe        Tsegaye \r\n                                    P.o. box       21937 \r\n                                    Code          1000 \r\n                                     Addis  Ababa \r\n                                      Ethiopia     \r\n \r\n',0,'2012-01-03 11:56:18','2012-01-03 11:56:18'),(95,83,'Newsletter Signup Form Submittal',0,'2012-01-03 22:48:03','2012-01-03 22:48:03'),(96,84,'NEEDY SCHOOLING GIRL IN KENYA\r\n\r\nNeedy school going girls can miss up to 40 school days in a year due to their menstrual cycle\r\nDuring my December holiday, I had to do some survey on a needy school girl in Kenya on the problems the face during their monthly circle.\r\n\r\nOBSERVATIONS.\r\n• Some needy girls dig through garbage dumps looking for used sanitary towels which they then wash and reuse exposing them to lots of disease.\r\n\r\n• Many girls in rural areas are even known to use leaves, dirty rags or even cow dung to try and stem their menstrual flow. (the cow dung is smeared on the panties and left to dry, then the girls puts it on)\r\n\r\n• This impedes their ability to compete in the classroom, leads to low self-esteem, higher drop-out rates and, in many areas of Kenya, makes them vulnerable to early marriage.\r\n\r\n• Along with the lost learning days, girls not surprisingly lose self-confidence, and their chance of rising to the top of their class drops farther each month.\r\n\r\n• It is common to tear old and use that fabric as a sanitary pad, but the resulting chaffing often causes extremely painful and embarrassing boils to develop\r\n\r\nChallenge\r\n• The girls enrolled in school may drop out before completing primary school – at least 100 of these are girls. Kenyan adolescent girls miss approximately 3 to 5 days learning days per month due to lack of funds to purchase sanitary pads.\r\n\r\n• Most of these girls will join the ranks of the unemployed, standing now at over 54% in Kenya and will undoubtedly remain throughout their lives amongst the 58% living in absolute poverty. The great potential they had before adolescence is blotted out, and their children will more than likely repeat this cycle.\r\n\r\n• Currently, women constitute the majority (58%) of illiterate adult Kenyans, with a significant reason being their own inability to complete school for many of the reasons listed here among others. The focus on girls’ education is timely, because there is an astonishing future earning potential on a national and household level investing in girls’ education in Kenya. This problem is sure to escalate, and there is currently no lasting solution to address these growing needs for girls or growing environmental crisis from all the sanitary pad waste.\r\n\r\nTHE FACTS\r\nCURRENT CHALLENGES FACING THE KENYAN GIRL\r\n1. 150 million school children may drop out before completing primary school\r\n2. 1,454,600 of these are known menstruating girls between 6th grade and high school\r\n3. 868,000 (three fifths) miss four to five days of school per month due to lack of sanitary pads and/or underwear .\r\n4. 4 to 5 learning days per month are missed by Kenyan adolescent girls\r\n5. 58% of Kenyans are living in absolute poverty\r\n6. 58% of adult Kenyans are illiterate, the majority being women\r\n\r\nBENEFITS OF KEEPING GIRLS IN SCHOOL\r\n• Improved income: One extra year of education beyond the average boosts eventual wages by 10-20% with primary school returns 5-15% and secondary education 15-25%.\r\n\r\n• Reducing HIV rates: A Kenyan study indicated that girls who stay in school are four times less likely to be sexually activity than those who drop out, reducing the incidence of HIV and early pregnancy dramatically.\r\n\r\n• Enhancing women’s choices over family planning: Doubling the proportion of women with a secondary education empowers women to better plan their families, resulting in smaller families from 5.3 to 3.9 children per woman (Kenya has one of highest birth rates globally, over 3%, placing a larger burden on young mothers).\r\n\r\n• Reducing infant mortality: An extra year of education reduces infant mortality 5-10% Reduced teen pregnancy: 40% of adolescent girls in Kenya with no education are pregnant versus 26% of those who completed only primary and only 8% of those with secondary education or higher (note: 40% of deaths from botched abortions are adolescent girls.\r\n\r\nAll this can be changed by supporting a girl child to go to school. Your donation can make a lifetime difference in a life of a girl. \r\n\r\nTo buy a sanitary pad for a girl, or sponsor a girl\'s education, please contact us on:\r\nEmail: vigilantlady2011@gmail.com, vigilantlady07@yahoo.com. or \r\nMpesa: +254- 0721-572794.',0,'2012-01-05 11:04:25','2012-01-05 11:04:25'),(97,81,'What a pleasant surprise to hear so soon from you. My heart is filled with hope and gratitude for the future . This is all because of your support. I was so excited I don\'t remember the ladies name , but she was very nice. Please accept my thanks and God bless.  Linda',0,'2012-01-05 15:21:50','2012-01-05 15:21:50'),(98,85,'hello,\r\nI have a question, somwhere I had heard that people can get comfort kits from you and put them together and knot them? Is this correct? \r\nTHank you!\r\nJoanna Martin ',0,'2012-01-05 16:49:38','2012-01-05 16:49:38'),(99,86,' I was needing the instructions on making school kits. We have made a lot of quilt kits and school kits but lost the instructions. Also if I could have the ones for layette bundles and hygene kits. Thank you',0,'2012-01-05 20:28:01','2012-01-05 20:28:01'),(100,87,'Newsletter Signup Form Submittal',0,'2012-01-06 08:30:05','2012-01-06 08:30:05'),(101,88,'Hello,\r\n\r\nArlyn Kauffman calling. I am traveling to Nicaragua next week with a study team from college. We are spending two weeks on the outskirts of Managua working with poor people under Outreach International. I am curious to know who is at CAM Managua at this time. DO they have email access? If yes, I would like to contact them and at least find out how close to them we will be working, and maybe even stop in for a visit.\r\n\r\nSo, if it\'s ok, could you forward me their email address? \r\n\r\nThanks,\r\nArlyn Kauffman\r\nWeldon, IA \r\n641.414.4470',0,'2012-01-06 14:47:02','2012-01-06 14:47:02'),(102,89,'We are moving down the road on January 14th.  We receive the newsletters and I just wanted our address changed.\r\n\r\nPlease change it to:\r\n1613 Division Hwy\r\nEphrata, PA  17522\r\n\r\nThanks.\r\n\r\nGalyn Graber',0,'2012-01-06 16:32:21','2012-01-06 16:32:21'),(1