ust get redirected.   I don’t know what to do, it is freezing outside and there is snow on the ground.  I ask myself where will we sleep, will we be cold, will we be hungry?   Will anyone Care? \r\n \r\nWe are a family of five Samantha (Mother), Robert (Father), Christopher (Son), Gabriel (Son), Samantha Jo (Daughter) and our little dog Sancho.  In February 2011 I lost my job due to medical reasons making it unable for me to work.  I have several different conditions which make it impossible for me to keep a job I have livedo reticularis ,  Raynaud phenomenon and rheumatoid arthritis. My husband has been looking for work ever since we arrived in Illinois 2008 and has only found temporary seasonal work,  which puts us back in the same situation at the of every seasons employment.  Even when working my husband Robert continues to seek permanent fulltime employment.  My son Gabriel is in his last year of high school and in a few months will graduate.  It has been his dream to graduate high school, he has strived to get here and I don’t know where we will be.  I have a young daughter with social phobia currently not in school and would like to get here the help she so desperately needs.  My oldest son just lost his job and  we cannot make ends meet we struggle to make it day to day.  I strive everyday looking for new ways to help my family, it is so hard to feed people with no money.  Recently my home phone was disconnected and that didn’t help.  I try and keep my spirits up because my children need to see me be Positive that way they really don’t have to experience the pain I feel deeply in my heart.  Life is hard enough and this is something that they did not ask for and as a parent I feel the need to protect them from this.  So I awake with a smile and tell them tomorrow will bring only bigger and better things.  I have to hold onto that.\r\nWe are now are facing an eviction (my court date is January 26, 2012) and no means of employment for our family has left us with no choice but to reach out to anybody that can help us, I am not ashamed of my situation and know that we will get back on our feet again, I have overcome many obstacles.  But this time I am having trouble making it to my knees to stand if you know what I mean.  I am desperately seeking help with finding a place to live and a fulltime employment opportunity for my family members.  We need some help (I will swallow my Pride for my family) in becoming independent and self-sufficient so we can keep our family together.   We are a Strong, Loving, Determined and Ambitious bunch and will not be separated; we are an awesome dedicated Team.  So please if you can help or know of someone who can Please Reach out to us in our time of Need.   I keep Matthew 7:7 close to my heart: Ask, and it shall be given you; seek, and ye shall find; knock, and it shall be opened unto you: \r\nSincerely,\r\nSamantha Swortwood\r\nEmail:  samanthaswortwood@gmail.com     r.swortwood@gmail.com\r\nAddress:  5422 West Woodland Drive McHenry, Illinois 60050(Not sure how long we will be here)\r\nHome:              (815)528-7471       (NOW DISCONNECTED)  Cell:              (815)271-1722      (STILL IN SERVICE)',0,'2012-01-25 05:46:20','2012-01-25 05:46:20'),(157,151,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-01-25 11:35:33','2012-01-25 11:35:33'),(158,152,'Newsletter Signup Form Submittal',0,'2012-01-25 16:55:23','2012-01-25 16:55:23'),(159,153,'My coworker’s father died and they only have half of the money for the funeral. I am trying to raise $2800 so they can have the burial ASAP (he passed away Monday night after contracting MRSA). Do you offer assistance for this circumstance?  I am reaching out to several organizations and understand that yours may not offer help for this particular circumstance, but it doesn\'t hurt to ask!\r\n\r\nThank you for your time,\r\nBeth',0,'2012-01-25 17:30:18','2012-01-25 17:30:18'),(160,154,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-01-25 21:10:45','2012-01-25