m.We also encouraging the women those who are working as a maid servant in the Muslims houses.We are providing them the sewing skill that they can earn and fulfill their needs.\r\nWomen in Pakistan\r\nWomen are one of the most disadvantaged groups in society in the Pakistan. Yet they are incredibly precious to their Heavenly Father who created them, as well as one of God\'s greatest resources for transforming communities. That’s why An Interrupted Life Ministry  has several ways impacting the lives of women:Pam’s Sewing Center and Alishba Sewing Center are running through the An Interrupted Life Ministry that provide a 6 month course  where poor women are taught to make traditional Pakistani  clothes as well as embroidery and soft toys.Students range in age from fifteen to forty-five. At the end of the course, each woman is presented with a treadle or hand-operated sewing machine at their graduation service.With the ability to generate an income, these women achieve a new level of dignity and status in the community- along with the security of knowing that they can help provide nourishing food, education, and health care for their children.As important as all these things are, the greatest gift these women receive is the gift of God - the good news of Jesus Christ. Before each tailoring lesson, a short devotion is given. For most of them they have heardthe Word of God first time that heavenly father loves them. and many have responded to that love.The both centers make a real difference in the lives of women!The women who graduated:\r\n• 40% receive Jesus as their Savior, and many of their families are also saved and started regularly to attend the local church.\r\n\r\n• 50% are able to earn an income as a result of their training; others save considerable amounts of money by sewing for their families.\r\n\r\n • Some become instructors and pass on the skills to other women what they have learned.\r\n\r\nRequest\r\nWe have two sewing centers 1-Pam’s sewing center and 2-Alishba Sewing center,Pam’s Sewing center is running very good and Alishba Sewing center had closed because we have no funds for pay salary to teacher and electricity bills and needs the center.You are requested for help to continue run the sewing center and ministry for win the souls.In each session many many women receiving the word of God and receiving Lord as their personal savior and learning skill to earn for their families.So it can sustain with your help and prayers.Hope for your loving response.\r\n\r\nBlessings,\r\n\r\nPastor Asif Raza\r\n\r\nAn Interrupted Life Ministry of Pakistan\r\n\r\nwww.aninterruptedlife.com',0,'2012-02-05 15:20:24','2012-02-05 15:20:24'),(215,197,'\r\nGreetings in Christ !\r\n\r\nwe are ....An Interrupted Life Ministry of Pakistan\r\n\r\n Vision:\r\n\r\n The purpose of this ministry is to help others, in their brokenness, understand that they do not have to lead a broken life.We believe every life has great value. Recovery from loss allows you to find that meaning and value and add joy to your life.\r\n\r\n “For I know the plans I have for you’’ Says the Lord “They are plans for good and not for disaster, to give you a future and hope.” Jeremiah 29:11\r\n\r\n Introduction:\r\n\r\n We are non-profit ministry in Pakistan, struggling to uplift the Christian families which don’t have any means to earn their daily food and have many children and unable to feed them.We also encouraging the women those who are working as a maid servant in the Muslims houses.We are providing them the sewing skill that they can earn and fulfill their needs.\r\nWomen in Pakistan\r\nWomen are one of the most disadvantaged groups in society in the Pakistan. Yet they are incredibly precious to their Heavenly Father who created them, as well as one of God\'s greatest resources for transforming communities. That’s why An Interrupted Life Ministry  has several ways impacting the lives of women:Pam’s Sewing Center and Alishba Sewing Center are running through th