 Ministry of Pakistan\r\n\r\nwww.aninterruptedlife.com',0,'2012-02-05 15:20:29','2012-02-05 15:20:29'),(216,198,'Could you please send me information on your summer Bible school offering projects? This would be on behalf of Kane Mennonite Church. Thanks!',0,'2012-02-05 21:43:32','2012-02-05 21:43:32'),(217,199,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-02-06 04:38:27','2012-02-06 04:38:27'),(218,200,'Sir / Ma\'am, I would like to receive information about any upcoming grant cycles.  I am building an organization that will be reaching out to Central America, including providing vocational training for orphans, coordinating mission trips and emergency giving throughout Central America and the Caribbean, taking advantage of micro economics to help the disadvantage and fight the drug trade (mostly in farming), lastly provide missionaries and ministry leaders a sabbath by providing them a vacation to Belize.  The country of Belize has offered to help build this organization by limiting import taxes, providing government leased land and providing local expertise.  I would love the opportunity to explain more or provide an executive summary if you are interested.\r\n\r\nIn Christ,\r\n\r\nAaron Godbey',0,'2012-02-06 18:48:48','2012-02-06 18:48:48'),(219,201,'I wondered if you have any jobs for maybe two weeks or so?  I have my job, but I would like to use my vacations to serve somewhere.  My interest would be to maybe work in an orphanage or somewhere among babies and small children.  But I’m guessing there you will have long term workers, right?  I just thought I’d ask.  I’m searching my heart about where God would want to use me.  Just answer according to your time and convenience.  Thank you and God bless you!',0,'2012-02-06 20:07:41','2012-02-06 20:07:41'),(220,202,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-02-06 20:12:32','2012-02-06 20:12:32'),(221,203,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-02-06 21:06:15','2012-02-06 21:06:15'),(222,204,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-02-07 02:41:52','2012-02-07 02:41:52'),(223,205,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-02-07 05:53:51','2012-02-07 05:53:51'),(224,206,'Hello and praise Jesus. Well my names are Rev. Shandrack from Nairobi Kenya. Am married to one wife by the name Esther and we are blessed with two sons that is Wonder and Wise. My wife Esther and i are the founders of Jehovah El-shaddai Ministries and our vision is reaching out to the unreached with the gospel of Christ, planting churches where there are no churches and helping the needy children especially whose parents died of AIDS. By the grace of God we now have planted 18 churches here in Kenya for the past six years and we have one children home with 17 children and we are really thankful to God for this. This time we approach you because of the need we have for our children. Because of the high cost of living we are unable to feed our needy children. It now cost 400 dollars to feed all our children per month. We therefore request you to pray for us and support us if possible. Your prayers and support can help us place a BIG smile in the faces of these little needy children.\r\n Thank you so much, we will be happy hearing from you and even know that you are praying for us. Thanks and remain blessed.\r\nYours,\r\nRev. Shandrack M. Katue',0,'2012-02-07 09:07:07','2012-02-07 09:07:07'),(225,111,'We live really close to CAM.  I was wondering if there was a program where my family and I could come to help out.  How does it work to come and pack supplies/clothes?\r\n\r\nI have an 11 month old and a 3 year old.  The three year old loves to help and she is really good at helping and taking instruction from her father and I.  The baby I could put in a backpack designed for babies.\r\n\r\nWe really would like to help.  My husband grew up helping out at CAM.  His father, David Yoder has been a supporter for decades now.\r\n\r\nMy husband is good friends with John Nolt, I believe he is a board member at CAM.\r\n\r\nI just thought I should ask about your rules on bringing children.\r\n\r\nI also sew if that would help.\r\n\r\nThanks.\r\n\r\nErin Yoder',0,'2012-02-07 13:05:46','2012-02-07 13:05:46'),(226,207,'Newsletter Signup Form Submittal',0,'2012-02-08 13:53:11','2012-02-08 13:53:11'),(227,208,'\r\nDEAR CAM,\r\n\r\nChristian greetings the name of Our Savior and Lord Jesus Christ. I hope this finds you all well.\r\n\r\nI would like to introduce our country and the Bible Missionary Church. Our Country is called MYANMAR formally known as BURMA. Our neighboring countries are India, Thailand, Bangladesh, China and Laos. Our country is populated about 60 millions and the 10/40 window country of dominated by the Buddhists. I am writing this letter to you with great hope and anticipate that you would write back to me with your valuable advice and encouragement for our mission work here in Myanmar.\r\n\r\nI am glad to know your your organization and is introduced by one of my Mennonite friends  who lives in USA. He strongly advised me to contact you and have partnership with you for to extend the Kingdom of God in Myanmar.\r\n\r\nWe are definitely committed to saturating Evangelism and Church Planting among the Unreached people. The BMC is established in 1997 and now  several churches are planted among the responsive people. We are also doing the orphans caring center and also have a small Bible Teaching Club for our people\r\nand the church planters. Our organization is well structured under the constitution of the General Conference/church. The General Conference consists in three district conferences and departments like Mission, Youth, Women, General Board and Executive Committee etc...We , BMC, are the full member of WORLD MENNONITE CONFERENCE (MWC).\r\n\r\nOur General Board has recently decided to find out the sound Organization  those who have the same belief/doctrines with us and will connect to them. We strongly felt that we need\r\ninternational connection to promote the mission works in our country. This is the desire that The Bible Missionary Church is called to be a communion of of international Church linked to one another in a community of faith for fellowship, worship, service and witness.\r\n\r\nDo you have a vision to get involved the mission work in our the unreached Buddhist land? We covet your prompt concern and prayer for the Buddhist land. We are very much interesting to or connect to your ORG. Could you also visit our country and see how our work is doing? \r\n\r\nI therefore would like you to consider this desired request. I am looking forward to hearing from you.\r\n\r\n\r\nYours sincerely,\r\n\r\nRev. Amos Thang Chin\r\nThe Founding President\r\nBible Missionary Church of Myanmar\r\nPO Box 951\r\nYangon, Myanmar',0,'2012-02-08 15:29:39','2012-02-08 15:29:39'),(228,209,'Hello,\r\nI am a 20 years old girl from romania. I have 5 more sisters and 2 brothers and an amazing mother, our father didn`t care about us so much...so our mother raised us all by herself. but God loved us so much that He did not let my mother alone so He took care of us. And one of the ways He did that is through you- Christian Aid Ministries. I am so thankful and I wanted you to know this, and to know that I was thaught for a little age to pray for you, because you helped us so much. So, thank you! I also want you to know that I am a woman of God now...I am living for Him...and I am involved in mission too and I want to help other people like you did for me and my family. God Bless you, all. I am praying for you. ',0,'2012-02-08 17:54:01','2012-02-08 17:54:01'),(229,209,'Hello,\r\nI am a 20 years old girl from romania. I have 5 more sisters and 2 brothers and an amazing mother, our father didn`t care about us so much...so our mother raised us all by herself. but God loved us so much that He did not let my mother alone so He took care of us. And one of the ways He did that is through you- Christian Aid Ministries. I am so thankful and I wante