 Signup From New Account',0,'2012-02-21 17:05:50','2012-02-21 17:05:50'),(272,250,'Thoreau Navajo Outreach is a faith based, non-profit organization that provides outreach services to support rural families and at risk youth with much needed aid.  Thoreau Navajo Outreach expanded services when there were 14 suicides within a three-month period.  Alcoholism, poverty and cultural dislocation were contributing factors.  Poverty was the primary reason identified.  \r\nThoreau Navajo Outreach learned that the families who were impacted by the suicides were isolated from a variety of resources. Access to resources such as clothing and food stores, schools and medical facilities is a significant issue that most families in our areas face.  Accessible outreach agencies like ours become a vital resource to many families in need.  By providing clothing we minimize the effects of poverty as a family can then utilize their financial assets where it is most needed e.g. food, shelter and transportation to medical facilities and schools.  \r\nSince 2009 we have provided families in need with food boxes, gently used clothing, school supplies, shoes, wood bundles to heat homes, minor home renovations and gifts to children and elderly during the holidays. \r\nUnfortunately our small non-profit organization has been effected by our unpredictable national economy.  We have reached a roadblock in obtaining much needed used clothing to replenish our clothing closet.  We are also in need of building materials to renovate homes and non-perishable food items for our food pantry.  \r\nOur services are open to all in need regardless of race, sex, religion and income.  A majority of the families we serve reside in rural areas.  We have received a huge response where many have stated that without our local outreach program they would have not been able to clothe their family, which is why I am contacting you.  \r\nOur non-profit organization is in dire need of gently used clothing from infant to adult sizes.  I am hoping that your program might be able to partner with us and provide us the gently used garments we need to replenish our clothing closet. We can pay for shipping cost if required.  We ask that you help us make a difference in our community.\r\nPlease contact me at 505-862-7530 to discuss a partnership.\r\n',0,'2012-02-21 18:38:08','2012-02-21 18:38:08'),(273,251,'We are a conservative nondenominational Bible College in Kenya, Africa, that desperately needs a borehole for clean drinking water. we have done the survey for all the costs involved which can be made available to you upon request.\r\nreference: \r\nBob Stauffer, Rosedale Mennonite Missions.\r\nThank you.',0,'2012-02-22 08:55:42','2012-02-22 08:55:42'),(274,252,'\r\nGreetings,\r\n \r\n \r\n   We are a non-profit and interfaith group with the purpose of building bridges between nations and cultures. Our immediate aim is to help the children wherever they are to live a normal and a decent life. As we know that millions of children are traumatized by war, we realized that the best help possible for them is to demonstrate love and compassion through actual demonstration of care and interest in them especially, for those who were less fortunate and had suffered from the consequences of war whether physically, emotionally or developmentally. Thus our plan is to build a resource center that will collect second hand items-toys, wheelchairs, medical instruments, children books, play utencils and equipment, children cloths, etc. The resource center has a team of volunteer professionals who will repair and clean those items and send them to children who are in need and especially to those who suffer from war atrocities. Our hope that we will bring a smile and some hope for those who are less fortunate than many of us.\r\nOur call to all of you is to help us by denoting some of the items you find to be useful and repairable so we can reuse them for peace and healing purposes. And even we can pay 