 Sir or Madam,\r\n\r\nI would like to unsubscribe from the monthly CAM newsletter in order to reduce your cost.\r\n\r\nYours sincerely,\r\n\r\nMartin Grundner',0,'2012-03-08 17:30:47','2012-03-08 17:30:47'),(333,308,'My husband and I work with an organization, here in the States, called International Messenger, of Clearlake, Iowa.  One of their ministries is \"Joshua Project\" - an HIV/AIDS evangelistic outreach to teens and young adults afflicted with HIV in Resita and Timasoara, Romania. \r\n\r\nJoshua Project does medical outreach in two areas.  First, they have a dental clinic in Resita, at their youth center,  HIV infected people are refused access adequate dental care, in Romania, due to their disease, and most have very poor teeth (or none at all) due to the disease process. The dental clinic is in desperate need of disposable gloves.  \r\n\r\nSecondly, Joshua Project missionaries have an active, on-going ministry to individuals with late-stage HIV/full-blown AIDS.  These individuals literally live in the contagious disease hospital in Timasoara.  They are in desperate need for basic oral multivitamins.  \r\n\r\nThe Joshua Project missionaries, Andy & Tresha McKnight, have asked us to try and get 50 boxes of medium size disposable gloves and 100 bottles of multivitamins - 90 ct. each.  We are going to Romania on July 2, 2012, and could bring them with us, but I saw on your website that you have a contact party in Romania already.  If we provided the funding, is it possible to you to ship these supplies directly to Romania?  Please advise!  God bless your ministry.  Linda Brandt - 507-822-3097 (cell) - 507-427-2348 (home).',0,'2012-03-09 00:55:58','2012-03-09 00:55:58'),(334,309,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-03-09 05:24:32','2012-03-09 05:24:32'),(335,310,'',0,'2012-03-09 12:48:45','2012-03-09 12:48:45'),(336,311,'We had a spoltlight event at Liverpool John Moores University and I Have had a listen to your presenter for Christian Aid. I would like to be considered for your graduate programme. I am in my second year studying Criminology.\r\nI would appreciate to hear from you even if it means coming in as a volunteer.\r\nPlease kindly advice accordingly.',0,'2012-03-09 12:53:45','2012-03-09 12:53:45'),(337,312,'Dear Brothers and Sisters in Faith,\r\n\r\n\r\nWe thank the Lord for making us in connecting with you via this mean that we appreciate so much and consider a gift from him. We are an indigenous ministry loves the Lord and is passionate about sharing the word he places on our hearts with people across Yemen. We are always looking to grow in faith and working hard to be interactive in the local community. Although, we could not serve his kingdom in Yemen freely as sharing the good news is prohibited by the State, we try to be very close to people and share with them in different ways. We love to find out opportunities to serve in Yemen.\r\n\r\n\r\nIt is very important to inform you that we are in faith from long time and definitely accepted Jesus Christ as Lord and decided to exert my life to spread his love to all people. Of course, we are in huge problems with extremist Muslim clerics and officials, but we always pray for their way to know Jesus even they deal curtly with me. We feel the doors are opened by him and the Holy Spirit is working inside all hearts and minds here and we pray that he uses us in building his kingdom in this unreached area.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nDuring ten years, we  served with many foreign brothers and sisters serving in missionaries from USA, UK and some European countries and were very admire with their works for sharing the good news and decided to do the same in collaboration with global Christian-centered bodies and groups who have deep love for Yemen and the Middle East.\r\n\r\n\r\nWe are currently ready  to represent  your Church/organization  in Yemen. We have good relations with the local community and look forward to serving in a direct support from you depending on connecting people and making disciples. We seek building up bridges into the lives of others who so desperately need the love of Jesus Christ.\r\n\r\n\r\n\"All authority in heaven and on earth has been given to me. Therefore go and make disciples of all nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit, and teaching them to obey everything I have commanded you. And surely I am with you always, to the very end of the age\" (Matt 28:18-20, NIV).',0,'2012-03-09 17:21:06','2012-03-09 17:21:06'),(338,313,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-03-10 00:08:13','2012-03-10 00:08:13'),(339,314,'Hello\r\n\r\nI am Mrs Bintt Abin .A complete citizen of Philippines.\r\n\r\nMy dear friend, there is something important i will want you to handle for God,s Glory through the less privileged ones.can you?\r\n\r\nIf you can, please kindly get back to me for more details through my personal email address (abnn51@kimo.com).\r\n\r\nGod bless you.\r\n\r\nMrs Bintt Abin.',0,'2012-03-10 11:33:55','2012-03-10 11:33:55'),(340,316,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-03-11 04:13:36','2012-03-11 04:13:36'),(341,317,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-03-11 16:54:46','2012-03-11 16:54:46'),(342,318,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-03-11 17:07:52','2012-03-11 17:07:52'),(343,319,'Beloved Prayer Partner in Christ!!                                                          \r\n        Greetings in the Name of our lord and Savior Jesus Christ.\r\n      Well and Wish. I immensely delighted in contact through e-mail. Happy about your wide and enlarged ministries. I am praying for good health of you, your family and your wonderful ministries.  Please allow me,\r\n       I would like to introduce myself as M .Theodore Williams Babu (Acts 26; 22) I was born as 8th child, brought up by my parents in an orthodox and devoted Hindu family. After completing my collegiate education, I was working as a tutor in Madurai. At the same time my life