 us, but \r\nI\'m trying to get some information. My husband and I are from the North Texas area. In 2006 we moved our family up to Maine due to my husbands job. In 2010 he was laid off. So we came back home where he took a contract position. In the process we had to leave all of our belongings in storage in Maine. All of our furniture, clothing, holiday items, kitchen items etc.. The cost of moving everything down here is just to much for us at this time. The contract job that my husband has been in since July has ended. However, we are very blessed and excited that he has been offered a permanent position starting April 9. Our problem is that we have four children-ages 17, 16, 13 and 3. We purchased twin beds for the kids when we arrived back in Texas, and a few necessary items-towels, a few dishes, jackets.. Our oldest son is graduating in May, and we have struggled to keep up with any necessary things that he has been required to have. I have yet to pay off his cap/gown. We have been renting a home here in Abilene,Texas and we have one vehicle. We have cut out any unnecessary expenses. We\'ve been fine until now. We are trying to find temp. jobs until my husband begins his new job in April to be able to keep up with our rent. However, all of our children have outgrown their clothes and shoes and have worn out their socks. When we left Maine we packed three suit cases for the six of us. Thinking that we would have our own things fairly quickly. Is there any type of assistance for clothing for our children? Anything would do. We don\'t have a picky group. Currently our boys each have a pair of jeans that I wash daily. And our daughter has a pair of jeans that are on the tight side, but we\'ve managed to move the button over for them to work for her. We don\'t need much. I can wash their clothes daily. But we have realized that we need some help. Any information that you may be able to give us would be so appreciated!\r\n \r\nThank you so much!\r\n \r\nCarrie Taylo